{"id":"immer","term":"Immer","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Talkative. (1.) The head of the sixteenth priestly order (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 24:14\">1 Chr. 24:14</a>). (2.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 20:1\">Jer. 20:1</a>. (3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:37\">Ezra 2:37</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:40\">Neh. 7:40</a>. (4.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:59\">Ezra 2:59</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:61\">Neh. 7:61</a>. (5.) The father of Zadok (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:29\">Neh. 3:29</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 24:14","Jeremiah 20:1","Ezra 2:37","Nehemiah 7:40","Ezra 2:59","Nehemiah 7:61","Nehemiah 3:29"]}